20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.054f62b8-fca5-411b-943a-44a4bd7ce8c2.description=
Loops as many number of times as specified in the input, that is, counts from 1 to another number incrementing by 1 for each iteration.

Inputs\:
count - Number of loops to complete.
reset - If true, then the counter will restart counting from 1.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.

Responses\:
has more 	- Counting has not completed, one or more iterations are pending.
no more 	- Counting completed. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.
failure 	- Something went wrong.
20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.0656bd8b-5242-42c3-82b8-03539ec324b6.prompt=Access Key Id\: 20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.143a9cfe-6fa7-431e-a075-f54910205f83.prompt=Enter the Amazon Access Key ID\: 20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.5cec0c52-a176-49d9-a8aa-778413b6bc09.prompt=Access Key\: 20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.6e1549ca-e849-4ba5-b3aa-fa5d4a17fc20.description=
Lists and describes your conversion tasks. If you specify a list of conversion task IDs, only those are described. Otherwise, all of the existing conversion tasks are described.

Inputs\:
    taskIds - An optional list of conversion task IDs. If you specify this value, only the conversion tasks in the list are described.
Example\: import-i-fh95npoc, import-i-fh49y3vb
    delimiter - The delimiter used to separate list elements.	
Default value\: ','
    rowDelimiter - The row delimiter in the results table.
Default value\: the line separator for the current operating system
    colDelimiter - The column delimiter in the results table.
Default value\:';'
    accessKeyId - The ID of the secret access key associated with your Amazon AWS or IAM account.
    accessKey - The secret access key associated with your Amazon AWS or IAM account.
    proxyHost - The proxy server used to connect to Amazon.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port. You must either specify values for both  and  inputs or leave them both empty.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    serviceEndpoint - The endpoint to which requests are sent. 
Default value\: ec2.amazonaws.com
Examples\:  ec2.us-east-1.amazonaws.com, ec2.us-west-2.amazonaws.com, ec2.us-west-1.amazonaws.com, ec2.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com, ec2.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com, ec2.ap-northeast-1.amazonaws.com, ec2.sa-east-1.amazonaws.com
    securityToken - The security token that you must pass to use the temporary credentials. You can generate this by using operations from the Security Token Service folder. You can only use the token together with the temporary credentials generated by the same operations.

Results\:
    returnCode - This is the primary output. It is a code that determines the response that the operation uses. This specifies whether the operation is successful or fails.
    conversionTasks - A table with the following columns\: conversion task ID, expiration time, state (one of the following values\: active, cancelling, cancelled, completed), status message related to the conversion task, and either the import volume ID (returned if the task is for importing a volume) or the import instance ID (returned if the task is for importing an instance). Each row in the table corresponds to a conversion task. If a column’s result is empty, 'null' is returned instead. 
    returnResult - The complete xml response returned by Amazon.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully. See the Notes for troubleshooting information.

Notes\:
1. Unlike other Amazon operations, the ID of the request you sent to Amazon, using this operation is not retrieved by Amazon. Thus, the  output will contain an empty string for each run of the operation.
2. As with all Amazon EC2 operations, the results might not appear immediately.
3. For Region-Endpoint correspondence information, check all the service endpoints available at\: http\://docs.amazonwebservices.com/general/latest/gr/rande.html\#ec2_region
20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.7b61e484-8977-4041-9f62-699fa7d6e2c0.description=
Removes a file/folder

Input Parameters\:
source - full path to file or directory

Responses\:
success - file/directory removed successfully
failure - unable to remove file/directory
20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.94a653a9-454e-4f20-8b72-f51c6e327c0a.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal
20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.c4ec665b-3ec0-47a5-b26d-142dcb4eba55.prompt=Enter the Amazon secret Access Key\: 20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.c84b7c2f-d769-4281-b217-0f42e5aaa580.prompt=Task Id\: 20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.description=
Checks the status of a conversion task and if the task is completed it cleans the files used to perform the Import operation.

Inputs\:
    taskId - The conversion task id to be checked.
Example\: import-i-fhao5g5p
    accessKeyId - Access key ID of the bucket owner.
    accessKey - The secret access key of the bucket owner.
    proxyHost - The proxy server used to connect to Amazon.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port. You must either specify values for both  and  inputs or leave them both empty.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    serviceEndpoint - The endpoint to which requests are sent. 
    securityToken - The security token that you must pass to use the temporary credentials. You can generate this by using operations from the Security Token Service folder. You can only use the token together with the temporary credentials generated by the same operations.    
    deleteCreatedFiles - Specifies whether to delete the files generated by the OVF Export operation.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    thisFlowPath - The path to the flow that checks the status of the Import conversion task and cleans the results.
Default value\:  Library/Integrations/Amazon/EC2/VM Import/VMWare Windows Server 2008 Vm Import/Check Import Status
    centralHost - Hostname or IP address of the machine where the Export VM operation copied the OVF and VMDK files. This is the OO 10.x server where the Get Schedule Flow steps will run against.
    centralUsername - The username used to connect to the Central host.
    centralPassword - The password corresponding to the centralUsername user.
    centralPort - The port used to connect to the Central host.
    centralProtocol - The port used to connect to the Central host.
   
Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
20cf56df-fdca-4e82-bdc9-89ab6eaca287.ef47a698-c08d-4849-88ff-8b5d0d276a00.description=
Sleeps for the number of seconds specified in the input.

Inputs\:
seconds - The number of seconds to sleep.

Responses\:
success - Slept for the number of seconds given as input.
failure - Was unable to sleep for some reason.
